In the first type of mechanical attack, a small, high-velocity liquid jet is formed during the asymmetrical collapse of a vapor bubble. If orientation and proximity of the jets is proper, a damaging attack occurs on the metal surface, as shown in Figure 6-7. This is the most probable form of mechanical attack, and high-speed cinematography,

