\section*{Separation}

When reservoir fluids arrive at the topsides they enter the separation train. There may be multiple trains depending upon the production capacity of the vessel. A slug catcher may also be needed to protect the separation system from variations in the production streams. Slugging is the partial separation of gas and liquid phases in a multiphase flow line. Slugging is characterized by sudden drops and surges in liquid and gas volumes. These variations can be highly problematic for topsides processing facilities. Large and rapid variations in flow can induce excessive gas flaring, reduction of operating capacity and can trigger plant shutdowns. In situations where frequent

