\section*{Compressor Station:}

The compressor station is the engine that powers a gas pipeline. As the name implies, the compressor station compresses the natural gas (increases its pressure) thereby providing energy to move the gas through the pipeline. Pipeline companies install compressor stations along a pipeline typically every 40 to 100 miles. The size

