There are two valves at the inlet to the plant reducing station, providing 100\% operational redundancy. The inlet piping to the plant may be NPS 24 to 48 piping and hundreds of millions of standard cubic feet of gas will flow each day to meet the total LNG plant demand. This, coupled with at least a 218 psig (15 bar) differential pressure drop across the inlet letdown valves, can result in high noise and vibration generation. Noise attenuation trim is a requirement. Because of the line size, the flow, and the trim, the valve size may be anywhere from NPS 16 to 24 and rated at ASME CL600 or CL900. It will almost always be a fail-close valve.

